<br>
The only tip I have is to always be conscious of smearing, don't get lazy with your hand and slop it around everywhere. Just be careful and go back over everything with an eraser later.<br>
<br>
-ten <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=refleximage>Reflex Image</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/23/01 1:18:40 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://liquid2k.com/refleximage/Reflex1.jpg height="60" width="60"></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smearing your artwork</span><hr size=1> You can always get a rolling pin and put your palm on that, I hear that helps. <p>"When it comes down to it, I was no hero, no savior, no rebuilder.  I was just a man caught up in a series of events beyond my understanding."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udogtopus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dogtopus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/23/01 12:05:09 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.brainfreeze.org.uk/fightclub/dogtopus.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smearing your artwork</span><hr size=1> You could try a harder pencil. Or you could be a 4B rebel, like me...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Generally, if I've done some kick-ass art, and I don't want to smear it (maybe I've got to do more frames, or a background or something) I get some tracing paper and stick it over the top, making sure I wrap it round my sketchbook and sticking the tape onto the cardboard backing (not the paper; D'oh...!). Then I trim it with scissors so it masks the bit I want to keep safe. It's cool 'cos it protects your work, but you can still see what you did. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.buttonpusher.net/kindamanga">KINDAMANGA!</a> <BR>
<a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm21.showMessageRange?topicID=148.topic&start=1&stop=20">I need guns....</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udjsketch2k1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DjSketch2k1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/23/01 3:34:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smearing your artwork</span><hr size=1> you're right, teny. i hate drawing for 3 hours, then spending another 2 getting the pencil @#%$ off of my hand.... <p><b>when the going gets tough,  run like hell.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubigdoctord.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BigDoctorD</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/23/01 4:31:42 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.avitarcity.com/DoctorD/bear6_beatnika.gif height=105 width=110></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smearing your artwork</span><hr size=1> are you talking about while you're working, or when you're finished?<br>
<br>
when you're finished you can spray your work with fixative, which stops it from smearing....<br>
while you're working you can wear a pair of weight lifter's gloves, they're cheap, and they serve the purpose you want... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utsura.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tsura</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/23/01 6:12:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smearing your artwork</span><hr size=1> I find a 2H works best. I used to use a mechanical pencil and it finally struck that it smudged and allowed me to look at two pictures one one page. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
but 2H is what I'd reccomend. Don't use the soft stuff, 'cuz when you erase, it never completely goes away. <br>
