~melch~ <p><i>... and I'm not easily impressed... WOW! a blue car!<i>~ Homer Simpson</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ufutura2001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Futura2001</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/23/01 9:19:04 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.att.net/~polysin/Futura_Copy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: smearing your artwork</span><hr size=1> Get an Eisel, You get less distortion and you are forced to not rest your hand on the paper.  Good times.  Or, use quick drying india ink.  That stuff is jet black, and has just enough viscosity so that it does not run.<br>
